    },
    {
        "The cones respond to bright light and mediate high-resolution colour vision during daylight illumination (also called ": null
    },
    {
        "photopic vision": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Photopic_vision"
    },
    {
        "). The rod responses are saturated at daylight levels and don't contribute to pattern vision. However, rods do respond to dim light and mediate lower-resolution, monochromatic vision under very low levels of illumination (called ": null
    },
    {
        "scotopic vision": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scotopic_vision"
